    "However, the true potential of these networks lies in their scalability down to nanometric sizes, enabling ultralow power consumption 46 (around 13 µW/oscillator) and rapid convergence 49 (time to solution <1 µs) to optimal solutions with high accuracy within just a few oscillation cycles.",
